race.description: Country Motor Company Super Maiden Handicap
race.comment: NO NO YES (3) resumes today and has been switched to the Sydney stable of the prominent Price & Kent Jnr. barn. His two trials in readiness have been very good and his SP on debut stands out. Can resume on a winning note as he looks above average. KENNEDY COMPOUND (9) is on debut for the Bjorn Baker stable with Winona Costin in the saddle. She's been very impressive in her last two outings and she strikes a suitable race on debut. Can make an immediate impact. FIREPOP (8) will find this much easier than recent efforts as he's been racing in metropolitan company. The draw should see her get every chance in the run under Collett and she's expected to make her presence felt. HEY JUDE (5) can make an impression first-up with two trials under her belt. ROMANCASTLE (10) showed enough on debut to suggest a bold showing is on the cards second-up.
